    "title": {
      "rendered": "How to Add 2024 Nonprofit Tech for Good Certificates to Your LinkedIn Profile"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p>LinkedIn has grown to over <a href=\"https://news.linkedin.com/about-us#Statistics\">one billion members from 200 countries</a> worldwide. Launched in 2003, nearly half of that growth has occurred over the last five years. LinkedIn is an ideal platform for nonprofit professionals to grow their personal brand and curate an online profile for current and future employers, funders, and sponsors.</p>\n<p>Certifications are a key feature of LinkedIn Profiles and below is a tutorial on how to add <a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/certificate-programs/\">certificates offered by Nonprofit Tech for Good</a> to your LinkedIn Profile. There are few tricks to maximizing how certificates appear on your profile and in the LinkedIn Home feed.</p>\n<h2>1) Add your certificate to your LinkedIn Profile.</h2>\n<p>To begin, go to your profile &gt; Add profile section &gt; Recommended &gt; <span class=\"t-14 t-14--open t-black--light t-bold\">Add licenses &amp; certifications:</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/certificate-programs/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-38545 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Add-certification-to-Linkedin-profile-e1704036119577.png?resize=500%2C306&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"306\" /></a></p>\n<p>Enter the name of your certificate and then <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/nonprofitorgs\">follow Nonprofit Tech for Good on LinkedIn</a> to ensure that Nonprofit Tech for Good can be found in the &#8220;Issuing organization&#8221; field.</p>\n<p>The issue date can be found on your certificate and know that certificates issued by Nonprofit Tech for Good do not expire, so you can leave the expiration date field blank.</p>\n<p>Your Credential ID is also found on your certificate and the Credential URL (<a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Heather-Mansfield-Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate-2024-scaled.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">see example</a>) was provided when you completed the certificate program and your claimed your certificate.</p>\n<p>Next, add &#8220;Skills&#8221; relevant to the certificate program (Social Media Marketing, Fundraising, Nonprofit Technology, Digital Strategy, and Content Strategy, etc.) and then &#8220;Save.&#8221;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/How-to-Add-a-Certificate-to-Your-LinkedIn-Profile-Nonprofit-e1704112282573.png?ssl=1\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-38569 size-full aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/How-to-Add-a-Certificate-to-Your-LinkedIn-Profile-Nonprofit-e1704112282573.png?resize=500%2C544&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"544\" /></a></p>\n<p>Your certificate then appears on your profile with a direct link to your certificate hosted on Nonprofit Tech for Good.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/certificate-programs/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-38571 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate-for-Nonprofits-on-LinkedIn-1-e1704112453254.png?resize=500%2C149&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"149\" /></a></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s worth noting that you can also add a thumbnail to your certificate under the &#8220;Media&#8221; option [after Skills], but due to image dimension constrictions, your certificate thumbnail will be cropped. Upload your certificate in image format [right-click to download from your Credential URL] and decide whether you like your certificate listed on LinkedIn with or without the thumbnail.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/certificate-programs/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-38556 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Media-in-LinkedIn-e1704038289653.png?resize=500%2C140&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"140\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/certificate-programs/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-38573 size-full aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate-for-Nonprofits-on-LinkedIn-2-e1704112636935.png?resize=500%2C196&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"196\" /></a></p>\n<p>Finally, if you have taken both <a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/certificate-programs/\">certificate programs offered by Nonprofit Tech for\u00a0 Good</a>, you can add both to your LinkedIn Profile.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Digital-Marketing-Certificate-for-Nonprofits-on-LinkedIn-e1704113197127.png?ssl=1\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-38575 size-full aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Digital-Marketing-Certificate-for-Nonprofits-on-LinkedIn-e1704113197127.png?resize=500%2C277&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"277\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">2) Post your certificate to your network on LinkedIn.</h2>\n<p>After you &#8220;Save&#8221; your certification to your profile, LinkedIn prompts you to share your new certification with your network. Nonprofit Tech for Good recommends that you &#8220;Skip&#8221; this option and instead share your new certification directly from the home feed. The default sharing option prompted by LinkedIn only allows you to share your certificate as a &#8220;Celebration&#8221; which does not allow you to upload your certificate in image format. When you post directly from the home feed, however, you can upload your certificate in image format which tends to receive more engagement than celebration posts and graphics.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/certificate-programs/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-38563 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Sharing-Certificate-e1704044160526.png?resize=500%2C610&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"610\" /></a></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s worth noting that you can also post your new certificate as a &#8220;Celebration&#8221; from the home feed, but when you upload your certificate in image format to the celebration image field, it is cropped when shared. To avoid cropping, simply upload and post your certificate as an image post.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Our<strong>\u00a0</strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/earn-a-certificate-in-social-media-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/earn-a-certificate-in-social-media-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1653256738392000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1o7aYZXpgFGzJb7CozPKzZ\">Certificate in Social Media Marketing &amp; Fundraising</a> program covers the fundamentals of social media marketing and fundraising for your nonprofit. Participants will learn how to create a social media strategy, how to craft a content marketing plan, and current best practices for using social media for community engagement and fundraising.</p>\n<p>The program requires the completion of three webinars and costs a total of $100 USD. You can attend the webinars live or view the recordings. <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/earn-a-certificate-in-social-media-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/earn-a-certificate-in-social-media-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1653256738392000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1o7aYZXpgFGzJb7CozPKzZ\">Learn more &amp; register</a>!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/earn-a-certificate-in-social-media-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-37646 size-full aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-Certificate-in-Social-Media-Marketing-and-Fundraising-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=960%2C755&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"755\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-Certificate-in-Social-Media-Marketing-and-Fundraising-for-Nonprofits.png?w=1000&amp;ssl=1 1000w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-Certificate-in-Social-Media-Marketing-and-Fundraising-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C236&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-Certificate-in-Social-Media-Marketing-and-Fundraising-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=768%2C604&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/2024-Certificate-in-Social-Media-Marketing-and-Fundraising-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C39&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n",
